subject: Olympic Games (2008)
Boxing
lead_paragraph: Rau’shee Warren, the world champion flyweight, has decided to stay in the amateur ranks for four more years in an attempt to become the first three-time Olympian in United States history. Warren, a three-time national champion, was the first two-time American Olympic fighter in 30 years when he lost a 1-point decision in his Beijing opener.
